{"lemma":"ضارِبٍ","slug":"ضارِبٍ","root":"ض.ر.ب","root_slug":"ض-ر-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/ض-ر-ب","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["adj","verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n25706"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B6%D8%A7%D8%B1%D9%90%D8%A8%D9%8D"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to fight"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to speculate, to venture"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"active participle of ضَرَبَ (ḍaraba)","tags":["active","form-of","participle"]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/dˤaː.ra.ba/","/dˤaː.rib/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n25706","headword_ar":"ضَارِبٌ","root":"Drb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Beating, striking, smiting,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hitting:"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.:] act. part. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Daraba","text_ar":"ضَرَبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in all its senses]. (K, TA.) ―         -b2-  A she-camel"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that strikes her milker:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K:). or one"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which, having been submissive,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tractable, before conceiving, afterwards strikes her milker away from before her:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or [the pl.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DawaAribu","text_ar":"ضَوَارِبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies she-camels"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that resist after conceiving, and become repugnant, so that one cannot milk them."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b3-  Also, and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaAribapN","text_ar":"ضَارِبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, TA,) the former a possessive epithet [i. e. denoting the possession of a quality], and the latter a verbal epithet [i. e. an act. part. n.], (TA,) (tropical:)  A she-camel"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that raises her tail, and smites with it her vulva,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, A, in which latter only the pl. is mentioned,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and then goes:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DawaAribu","text_ar":"ضَوَارِبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (A, TA.) And the former is like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tDrAb","text_ar":"تضراب"},{"kind":"text","text":", [i. e. ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tiDoraAbN","text_ar":"تِضْرَابٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", as appears from what follows,] expl. by Lh as meaning (assumed tropical:)  A she-camel"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that has been covered by the stallion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and"},{"kind":"text","text":"app."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that raises her tail in consequence thereof,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"but respecting which one knows not whether she be pregnant"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tiDoraAbN","text_ar":"تِضْرَابٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies a she-camel"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"recently covered by the stallion"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and therefore often raising her tail"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Mz, 40th"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nwE","text_ar":"نوع"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b4-  The former ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaAribN","text_ar":"ضَارِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":") signifies also (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Swimming,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA,) in water. (TA.) Dhu-r-Rummeh says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"layaAliYa All~ahowi yaTobiyniY faA^atobaEuhu\n                      \n                     \n                        kaA^an~aniY DaAribN fiY gamorapK laEibu"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"In the nights of diversion he calls me and I follow him as though I were swimming in a deep water, sporting"},{"kind":"text","text":"therein]. (S, TA.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TayorN DawaAribu","text_ar":"طَيْرٌ ضَوَارِبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Birds seeking sustenance:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"birds traversing the land,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"migrating,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in search of sustenance."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, TA.) ―         -b6-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DariybN","text_ar":"ضَرِيبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b7-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaAribN","text_ar":"ضَارِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies (assumed tropical:)  A"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dark"},{"kind":"text","text":"night: (K:) or a night"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of which the darkness extends to the right and left, and fills the world."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O. [So in my copies of the S and in the O and TA: but accord. to Golius, as from the S, “ yet not filling the air. ”]) See the verse of Homeyd cited in the first paragraph. [J cites as an ex. of the last of the meanings expl. above, and so does Sgh in the O, the verse in the sentence here next following.] ―         -b8-  (assumed tropical:)  Anything"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"long:"},{"kind":"text","text":"applied in this sense to a night: thus in the following verse:"},{"kind":"quote","text":"waraAbaEatoniY taHota layolK DaAribi\n                      \n                     \n                        bisaAEidK faEomK wakaf~K xaADibi"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And that she helped me in lifting and putting on the loads, beneath"},{"kind":"text","text":"the darkness of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a long night, with a plump fore arm and a hand dyed with hinnà"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b9-  (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A place,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a depressed place,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a valley,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in which are trees."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K, TA.) And (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A piece of rugged ground extending in an oblong form in a plain,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"soft, tract."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA.) And (assumed tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"like of a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raHobap","text_ar":"رَحْبَة"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in a valley"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"where the water flows into it from its two sides:"},{"kind":"text","text":"see art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rHb","text_ar":"رحب"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DawaAribu","text_ar":"ضَوَارِبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.)"}],"source_refs":["S","K","TA","A"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}